I think in this case we can use double check locking

```
if (fd < 0) {
  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(openMutex);
  if (fd < 0) {
    open();
  }
}
```

why move `device` and `formats` to class data members? Seems like they are only used here. Maybe just keep them here and use constexpr instead?
```
constexpr int device = 0;
constexpr std::array<std::string_view, 3> formats = {"/dev/ipmi", "/dev/ipmi/",
                                              "/dev/ipmidev/"};
```
